In a #large pot{} or #dutch oven{} (5.5 qt), over medium-high heat, add chopped @bacon{6%oz} and sauté until browned ~{5-7 mins}.
Remove bacon to a paper-towel lined plate and spoon out excess oil, leaving about 1 Tbsp @oil{1%tbsp} in the pot.
Add @italian sausage{1%lb}, breaking it up with your spatula and sauté until cooked through ~{5 min}. Remove to paper towel lined plate.
Finely dice @onion{1} and add to the pot. Saute ~{5 min} or until soft and golden then add @minced garlic{10%cloves} and saute ~{1 min}.
Add 4 cups @chicken broth{4%cups} and 6 cups @water{6%cups}, and bring to boil. Add sliced @potatoes{5%medium sized one} and cook ~{13-14 min} or until easily pierced with a fork.
When potatoes nearly done, add chopped @kale{1%bundle} and cooked sausage and bring everything to a light boil.
Stir in 1 cup @cream{1%cup} and bring to boil.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper then remove from heat.
Garnish with bacon and @grated parmesan{to taste}.
